The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Wednesday, February 11, 2004 				 Asim bounty for roads
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Calcutta, Feb. 10: The government today released Rs 319 crore for the repair and improvement of 3,650 km of roads and 12 bridges. 																								After a meeting with the zilla parishad chiefs, finance minister Asim Dasgupta and PWD minister Amar Chowdhury announced the decision to release the money. This is an ongoing process and has nothing to do with the elections, Dasgupta said when asked if the generosity was in view of the Lok Sabha polls. 																								Asked why the major portion of the funds for the repair and improvement of roads was being released towards the end of the financial year, Dasgupta said: Road work is best done during this part of the year. Moreover, revenue collection also increases now. 																								Dasgupta met officials of Bankura, Purulia, West Midnapore, Burdwan and South 24-Parganas at Writers Buildings. The allocation for North 24-Parganas had already been discussed. The meeting with the officials of Howrah, Hooghly and Murshidabad was conducted through videoconferencing. 																								The work for which funds were released has to be started before the Election Commissions code of conduct comes into effect.
